cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CE

This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes an Adaptive Operator Selection (AOS) method based on Double Deep Q-Learning (DDQN), a Deep Reinforcement Learning method, to control the mutation strategies of Differential Evolution (DE). It also uses a neural network to predict which mutation strategy should be applied to each parent at each generation according to the DE state. 

It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses a Deep Reinforcement Learning method to control the parameters of an Evolutionary Algorithm. 

Additionally, it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes an adaptive method to improve the performance of an Evolutionary Algorithm. 

It could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category as it uses a control method to adjust the parameters of an Evolutionary Algorithm. 

Finally, it could belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category as it uses benchmark functions to evaluate the performance of the proposed method.
